commitResults.messageTitle: Make the code more OOP and update the save format of Deadline
commitResults.messageBody:
Extracted the following classes:
Ui: deals with interactions with the user
Storage: deals with loading tasks from the file and saving tasks in the file
Parser: deals with making sense of the user command
TaskList: contains the task list and operations to manipulate the list
Command: AddCommand, DeleteCommand, ListCommand, ExitCommand, UpdateCommand that inherit from an abstract Command class to write the main logic of the App

Update the save format of Deadline to remove the formatting of property "by"

Divide classes into packages
command:  AddCommand, Command, DeleteCommand, ExitCommand, ListCommand, UpdateCommand
duke: Duke, DukeException, Parser, Storage, Ui
task: Deadline, Event, Task, TaskList, Todo

Add Junit tests to test the behavior of the following classes' codes:
- Deadline
- Event
- Todo

commitResults.messageTitle: Sort tasks managed by the App
commitResults.messageBody:
Implement sorting of the tasks by type of tasks where Deadline comes first, followed by Event, followed by Todo. 

For Deadline:
* sort by due date 
* sort by description in ascending order

For Event & Todo: 
* sort by description in ascending order
Tweak padding, colors and background image of the dialog container to make the GUI more pleasing to look at
Fix Storage bug of not adding a new line when storing new task.
